{A38: Symmetrical English vs ...g6: 4 Bg2 Bg7 5 Nf3 Nf6} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3.
Bg2 Bg7 4. O-O O-O 5. c4 d6 6. Nc3 c5 7. d3 Nc6 8. Rb1 Ne8 9. Bd2 (9. a3 Nc7
10. Nd5 Rb8 11. b4 cxb4 12. axb4 b5 13. Be3 bxc4 14. dxc4 Bf5 15. Ra1 Bxa1 16.
Qxa1 e5 17. Bh6 Nxd5 18. cxd5 Nxb4 19. Bxf8 Qxf8 20. Qxa7 Ra8 21. Qb7 Rb8 22.
Qa7 Ra8 23. Qb7 Rb8 {Himanshu,S (2408)-Bai,J (2180) New Delhi 2012 1/2-1/2})
9... Bd7 $146 (9... Nc7 10. a3 (10. Qc1 Rb8 11. Bh6 Bd7 12. a3 a5 13. Nd5 b5
14. Nxc7 Qxc7 15. cxb5 Rxb5 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. d4 Bf5 18. Ra1 Qb6 19. d5 Nd4 20.
Qe3 Re8 21. Nd2 e5 22. Rac1 Qa6 23. Nc4 a4 24. f3 Rb3 {Greenfeld,A (2510)
-Cebalo,M (2475) Biel 1986 1/2-1/2 (81)}) 10... a5 11. Ne1 Bd7 12. Nc2 Rb8 13.
b4 axb4 14. axb4 b6 15. b5 Nd4 16. Nxd4 Bxd4 17. Qc2 f5 18. e3 Bg7 19. Ne2 g5
20. Bc3 e5 21. f4 Qe7 22. Qb2 Bc8 23. Ra1 Bb7 24. Ra7 {Enigl,K (2205)-Mahdy,K 
(2455) Austria 1995 0-1 (81)}) 10. a3 {Secures b4} a5 11. Qc2 Nc7 12. Na2 (12.
h4 Bg4 $11) 12... Qc8 13. b4 axb4 14. axb4 Nxb4 (14... Bg4 15. e3 $11) 15. Nxb4
cxb4 16. Bxb4 Ne6 17. Bc3 Bc6 18. Bxg7 Nxg7 19. Qb2 Qd7 20. Ra1 b5 $2 (20...
Ne6 $5 $14 {should not be overlooked}) 21. cxb5 (21. Rxa8 $142 Bxa8 22. cxb5
$16) 21... Bxb5 $2 (21... Rxa1 $142 $5 22. Rxa1 Qb7 $16) 22. Ne5 (22. Rxa8 $5 {
might be the shorter path} Rxa8 23. Ne5 dxe5 24. Bxa8 f6 $18) 22... Rxa1 23.
Nxd7 Rxf1+ 24. Kxf1 Bxd7 25. f4 Be6 (25... Rc8 26. Qb7 Rd8 27. d4 $18) 26. Kf2
(26. Qb7 $5 {seems even better} Nf5 27. Kf2 h5 $18) 26... Rc8 27. h3 h5 28. d4
Kf8 29. d5 Bd7 30. Qb4 Ke8 31. Qb2 {White threatens to win material: Qb2xg7}
Kf8 32. Kg1 Rd8 33. Kh2 Rc8 34. Qb7 Rd8 (34... Ke8 35. Bf3 $18) 35. Bf3 Ke8 36.
g4 hxg4 37. Bxg4 Bxg4 38. hxg4 Kf8 39. e4 Re8 (39... f6 40. Kg3 $18) 40. f5 (
40. e5 $142 $5 {makes it even easier for White} Rd8 $18) 40... gxf5 41. exf5 f6
42. Qb3 (42. Kg3 Kf7 $18) 42... Kf7 (42... Rc8 $5 $16) 43. Kg2 Rh8 44. Qe3 Rh7
45. Qf4 Rh4 46. Kg3 $4 {there were better ways to keep up the pressure} (46.
Qg3 $142 {and the scales tip in favour of White} Rh8 47. Qc3 $18) 46... Nh5+
$11 47. gxh5 Rxf4 48. Kxf4 {A pawn endgame occured} Kg7 49. Kg4 Kh7 50. Kh4 Kg7
51. Kg4 1/2-1/2

