{[%mdl 8256] D00: 1 d4 d5: Unusual lines} 1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nc6 4. Nf3
Bg4 5. Be2 (5. c3 e6 6. Qb3 Qc8 7. Nbd2 Nf6 8. Ne5 Be7 9. Nxg4 Nxg4 10. Be2 Nf6
11. O-O O-O 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13. Bg5 Nd7 14. Rac1 Qc7 15. Rfd1 Bd6 16. Nf3 Nde5
17. Nd4 Na5 18. Qc2 a6 19. e4 Ng6 {Kramnik,V (2785)-Gelfand,B (2736) Moscow
2007 1-0}) 5... e6 6. c3 (6. O-O Bxf3 7. Bxf3 cxd4 8. e4 dxe4 9. Bxe4 Nf6 10.
Bxc6+ bxc6 11. Be5 c5 12. c3 dxc3 13. Qa4+ Qd7 14. Qxd7+ Nxd7 15. Bxc3 f6 16.
Re1 Kf7 17. Nd2 Be7 18. Ne4 Nb6 19. Rac1 Rhd8 20. Ba5 Rac8 {Kovalenko,V (2198)
-Plat,V (2483) Prague 2013 0-1 (41)}) 6... Qb6 {Black threatens to win
material: Qb6xb2} 7. Qc1 $146 (7. Qb3 c4 8. Qc2 Nf6 9. h3 Bf5 10. Qc1 h6 11.
Nbd2 Qd8 12. O-O Be7 13. Bd1 g5 14. Bg3 Bd3 15. Re1 Ne4 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. Nd2
Bd6 18. Bxd6 Qxd6 19. b3 Na5 20. bxc4 Nxc4 21. Bc2 Nxd2 {Heinzel,O (2340)-Golf,
E (2205) Einhausen 2009 1-0 (43)}) 7... cxd4 8. exd4 (8. cxd4 Nge7 $11) 8...
Rc8 9. Nbd2 Nf6 10. h3 {White threatens to win material: h3xg4} Bh5 11. O-O Ne4
12. Be3 (12. Bd3 Nxd2 13. Qxd2 Bxf3 14. gxf3 Be7 $11) 12... f5 {Black has a
new backward pawn: e6} 13. Re1 Be7 14. c4 O-O 15. c5 {White threatens to win
material: c5xb6} Qd8 16. Nxe4 dxe4 (16... fxe4 17. Ng5 Bxg5 18. Bxg5 $15) 17.
Ng5 $11 Bxg5 18. Bxg5 (18. Bxh5 $2 {is not as innocent as it looks} f4 19. Qc4
fxe3 20. Qxe6+ Kh8 21. fxe3 Rc7 $19) 18... Qe8 19. Bb5 Qg6 20. Bxc6 Rxc6 21. b4
(21. Kh2 $5 $14) 21... h6 $11 {Black threatens to win material: h6xg5} 22. Bf4
Bf3 23. g3 Qh5 {Black has a mate threat} 24. Kh2 g5 25. Bd6 {White threatens
to win material: Bd6xf8} Bg4 26. h4 $4 (26. Rh1 $142 {this is the best way to
fight back} Rd8 27. Qa3 $11) 26... Rxd6 $19 27. cxd6 gxh4 28. Kg1 (28. Rh1 {
no good, but what else?} Bf3 29. Kg1 Bxh1 30. Qf4 hxg3 31. fxg3 $19) 28... hxg3
29. fxg3 Bf3 30. Qf4 Qh1+ (30... Qh3 $142 {and Black has prevailed} 31. Kf2 Rc8
$19) 31. Kf2 Qg2+ 32. Ke3 Qc2 33. Qxh6 (33. d7 {desperation} Qc3+ 34. Kf2 Qxd4+
35. Qe3 Qb2+ 36. Re2 Bxe2 37. Qc1 Qd4+ 38. Kxe2 Qd3+ 39. Ke1 Qxg3+ 40. Ke2 Qf3+
41. Kd2 e3+ 42. Kc3 $19) 33... f4+ $1 {Mate attack} 34. gxf4 (34. gxf4 Qc3+ {
Mate attack}) 34... Qd3+ 35. Kf2 Qd2+ (35... Qxd4+ $6 {is a useless try} 36.
Kg3 Rf7 37. Rg1 (37. Qxe6 $2 {fails because of} Qg7+ 38. Kh4 Kh8 39. Rxe4 Rf6
$19 (39... Qxa1 $4 {is refuted decisively by mate in 3} 40. Qh6+ Kg8 41. Re8+
Rf8 42. Rxf8#)) 37... Rg7+ 38. Kh3 Bg4+ 39. Rxg4 Qe3+ 40. Kh2 Qe2+ 41. Kh1 Qf3+
42. Kh2 Qe2+ 43. Kh1 Qf3+ 44. Kh2 Qe2+ $11) 36. Kg3 (36. Re2 {does not save
the day} Qxe2+ 37. Kg3 Qg2+ 38. Kh4 Qg4#) 36... Qg2+ (36... Qg2+ 37. Kh4 Qg4#)
0-1

