{[%mdl 8192] A34: Symmetrical English: 2 Nc3, lines with ...d5} 1. c4 c5 2. Nc3
Nf6 3. g3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Bg2 Nc7 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. e3 $146 {Consolidates d4} (
7. Rb1 e5 8. a3 Be6 9. O-O c4 10. Qa4 Bd6 11. d3 cxd3 12. Ng5 dxe2 13. Nxe2 Bf5
14. Ra1 O-O 15. Rd1 Qe7 16. Be3 h6 17. Ne4 Rfd8 18. Nxd6 Rxd6 19. Rxd6 Qxd6 20.
Rd1 Qg6 21. Rc1 Bd3 {Matthias,H (2376)-Nikula,R (2333) Germany 2003 1-0 (34)})
(7. Qa4 $142 $5 Bd7 8. O-O $14) 7... e5 $11 {White has a cramped position.
White's piece can't move: c1} 8. O-O {White castles and improves king safety}
Bg4 (8... Be7 9. Qa4 O-O 10. Rd1 $15) 9. Qc2 {White has a cramped position.
White's piece can't move: c1} (9. Qb3 Rb8 $11) 9... Qd7 10. d3 (10. Ne4 $5 Ne6
11. Qc4 $11) 10... O-O-O $15 {Black has a very active position} 11. Ne1 Bh3 12.
a3 {Prevents intrusion on b4} (12. Bxh3 $5 Qxh3 13. Ne4 $15) 12... Bxg2 $17 13.
Kxg2 g5 (13... Be7 14. b4 cxb4 15. axb4 Bxb4 16. e4 $17) 14. Ne4 {White
threatens to win material: Ne4xc5. White forks: c5+g5} Qd5 15. f3 Be7 16. Bd2 (
16. Nxg5 f5 (16... Bxg5 $143 17. e4 Nd4 18. Qc3 $11) 17. Nh3 Rhg8 $15) 16... h5
{White has a cramped position. White's piece can't move: e1} (16... f5 17. Nf2
$17) 17. Nc3 (17. Rc1 $142 $5 {is noteworthy} h4 18. Nxc5 hxg3 19. hxg3 Bxc5
20. Qxc5 $15) 17... Qd7 $17 18. Rd1 h4 19. g4 f5 20. h3 e4 (20... f4 $142 $5
$17) 21. dxe4 $11 Qd6 (21... fxg4 22. fxg4 Rhf8 $11) 22. f4 $4 {allows the
opponent back into the game} (22. e5 $142 Nxe5 23. Qxf5+ Kb8 24. Ne4 $16) 22...
fxg4 $15 23. hxg4 h3+ {Pushes the passed pawn} 24. Kg3 $2 (24. Kh1 $142 {
and White is still in the game} gxf4 25. exf4 $15) 24... gxf4+ $19 25. exf4
Bh4+ (25... Nd4 $142 $5 26. Qd3 Qd7 $19) 26. Kh2 $17 Nd4 {Black threatens to
win material: Nd4xc2} 27. Qd3 {White threatens to win material: Qd3xh3} Qd7 (
27... Qe6 28. f5 Qb3 29. e5 $15) 28. f5 {White gains space} (28. g5 $5 $11 {
has some apparent merit}) 28... Rdg8 $15 29. Bf4 Rxg4 30. Rd2 $4 (30. Be5 $142
{was necessary} Rhg8 31. Bxd4 cxd4 32. Qxd4 $17) 30... Bxe1 $19 31. Rd1 (31.
Rxe1 {doesn't improve anything} Rxf4 32. Kh1 Rg4 $19) 31... Bxc3 (31... Qg7 32.
Rd2 Rg2+ 33. Kh1 Bxd2 34. Bg3 Rxg3 35. f6 Qg5 36. f7 Rxd3 37. f8=R+ Rxf8 38.
Rxf8+ Kd7 39. Rf7+ Ke6 40. Rf2 Be3 41. Nb5 Rd1+ 42. Kh2 Bf4+ 43. Rxf4 Qg2#) 32.
bxc3 Nd5 {Black threatens to win material: Nd5xf4} (32... Rg2+ $142 {nails it
down} 33. Kh1 Qg7 $19) 33. Be5 $17 Qc6 $4 {instead of simply winning the game}
(33... Nf6 $142 $1 34. cxd4 Qf7 $15) 34. cxd4 $18 (34. Bxh8 $6 {is clearly
weaker} Qc7+ 35. Kh1 Rg3 36. cxd4 Rxd3 37. Rxd3 Qh7 $14) 34... c4 35. Qf3 (35.
exd5 $142 {seems even better} Qxd5 36. Qf3 Rg2+ 37. Kh1 Qxf3 38. Rxf3 $18)
35... Qa4 $4 {causes even greater problems} (35... Nf6 36. d5 Qb6 $18) 36. Bxh8
$18 Qc2+ (36... Rf4 {hardly improves anything} 37. Qe2 Nc3 $18) 37. Kh1 (37.
Rf2 $142 {secures victory} Qxe4 38. Qxe4 Rxe4 39. f6 Nxf6 40. Rxf6 $18) 37...
Qg2+ $11 38. Qxg2 hxg2+ {Black forks: f1.} (38... Rxg2 $4 39. exd5 Rg8 40. Be5
$18) 39. Kg1 $4 {White is ruining his position} (39. Kh2 $142 gxf1=Q 40. Rxf1
Rxe4 41. Be5 $11) 39... Ne3 $4 {simply marches past the door to victory} (39...
gxf1=Q+ $142 {finishes off the opponent} 40. Kxf1 Ne3+ 41. Ke2 Nxd1 42. Kxd1
Rxe4 $19) 40. Rfe1 (40. Rf3 $142 {secures the point} Nxd1 41. f6 Kd7 $18 (41...
Rxe4 42. f7 Re1+ 43. Kxg2 Re2+ 44. Kf1 Rf2+ 45. Rxf2 Kd7 46. Rf3 Nb2 47. f8=Q
Nd1 48. Rf7+ Ke6 49. Qe7+ Kd5 50. Qe5+ Kc6 51. Qc5#)) 40... Nxd1 41. Rxd1 Rh4
42. Kxg2 Rxh8 43. Kg3 (43. e5 {makes it even easier for White} Kc7 44. f6 Rh6
$18) 43... Kd7 44. e5 Rc8 (44... a6 45. d5 c3 46. Rc1 $18) 45. Kf3 (45. d5 c3
46. f6 c2 $18) 45... c3 46. Rc1 Rc4 (46... c2 $18 {otherwise it's curtains at
once}) 47. Ke3 b5 (47... c2 {doesn't get the bull off the ice} 48. Kd3 Ra4 49.
Rxc2 Rxa3+ 50. Ke4 $18) 48. Kd3 (48. Kd3 Rc8 49. Rxc3 $18) 1-0

