{[%mdl 8256] D10: Slav Defence: 3 cxd5 (without early Nf3) and 3 Nc3} 1. d4 d5
2. c4 c6 3. e3 Nf6 4. h3 $146 {Prevents intrusion on g4} (4. Nd2 Bf5 5. Ngf3 e6
6. Be2 Bd6 7. c5 Bc7 8. b4 Nbd7 9. Bb2 Ne4 10. Nxe4 Bxe4 11. O-O Qf6 12. Nd2
Qh6 13. f4 f5 14. Nxe4 fxe4 15. b5 O-O 16. Qa4 e5 17. dxe5 Bxe5 18. Bxe5 Nxe5 {
Reti,R-Spielmann,R Teplitz Schoenau 1922 1-0 (34)}) (4. Qc2 Bg4 (4... g6 5. Bd3
Bg7 6. Nd2 (6. Nf3 O-O 7. O-O dxc4 8. Bxc4 Bf5 9. Qe2 Nbd7 10. Nh4 Bxb1 11.
Rxb1 e5 12. Nf3 exd4 13. exd4 Nb6 14. Bb3 Re8 15. Qc2 Nfd5 16. Bg5 Bf6 17. Bh6
Bg7 18. Bd2 Qd6 19. Rbd1 Nf4 20. Qc5 Qf6 {Kortschnoj,V (2630)-Lieb,H (2275)
Berlin West 1985 1-0}) 6... O-O 7. Ngf3 a6 8. O-O Nbd7 9. h3 e6 10. a4 b6 11.
b4 Re8 12. Bb2 Bb7 13. c5 bxc5 14. bxc5 a5 15. e4 dxe4 16. Bxe4 Nd5 17. Nc4 Ba6
18. Rfc1 Bxc4 19. Qxc4 {Vokoun,J (2208)-Kohout,V (2197) Czechia 2010 0-1 (48)})
5. Nc3 e6 6. Bd3 Nbd7 7. Nge2 Bh5 8. cxd5 cxd5 9. Qb3 Rb8 10. Ng3 Bg6 11. Bxg6
hxg6 12. e4 Nb6 13. e5 Nfd7 14. Nge2 Nc4 15. g3 b5 16. O-O Be7 17. Kg2 Qc7 18.
h4 Qc6 {Kortschnoj,V (2615)-Ivanchuk,V (2710) Monte Carlo 1994 0-1 (42)}) (4.
Nc3 g6 $14) 4... b6 (4... Bf5 5. Nf3 $11) 5. Nf3 $14 a5 6. Bd3 b5 (6... Ba6 7.
b3 $16) 7. cxb5 $16 cxb5 8. Bxb5+ Nbd7 9. Nc3 e6 10. O-O Bd6 11. a4 {White has
a new backward pawn: b2} (11. Bd2 O-O $16) 11... O-O 12. Qc2 Re8 (12... Bb7 $5
$14 {looks like a viable alternative}) 13. e4 $16 Bb7 $4 {solves nothing} (
13... dxe4 $142 14. Nxe4 Nxe4 15. Qxe4 Rb8 $16) 14. e5 $18 Qc7 15. exd6 Qxd6
16. Ne5 $1 {Deflection: d7} Bc8 (16... Nxe5 17. Bxe8 {Deflection Pinning}) 17.
Bg5 1-0

